{"questionId":"32041736","questionHtml":"<p>In 2008, there were no beavers in Scotland, as they had become extinct. In 2009, beavers were introduced from Norway. Surveys were carried out in the region of Tayside to monitor the beaver population.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/dbe51773173a543c966b32480cb6c833047e54e6.png\" width=\"141\" height=\"121\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><sup>[Source: animatedfunk, n.d. Beaver Illustrations – stock illustration [image online] Available at: <a href=\"https://www.gettyimages.co.uk/detail/illustration/beaver-illustrations-royalty-free-illustration/1453231718\">https://www.gettyimages.co.uk/detail/illustration/beaver-illustrations-royalty-free-illustration/1453231718</a> [Accessed 30 November 2023].Source adapted.]</sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It is believed that the population, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> , grows according to a logistic model</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>,</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the number of years after <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2008</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A survey in 2017 estimated the population to be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>433</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>A survey in 2020 estimated the population to be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>954</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Find the carrying capacity, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>, for the number of beavers in Tayside, according to this model.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>433</mn></math>&nbsp; (<strong>OR </strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>954</mn></math>)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>433</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>954</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to rearrange into linear form or substitute for <em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>433</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></msup><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi></math> </strong></em>&nbsp; and&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>954</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></msup><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi></math></strong></em><strong> &nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>954</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>433</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></msup><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>attempt to solve simultaneously (e.g. graph or eliminate <strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math></em></strong>)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>306</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>187</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>11100</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>11100</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept a correct decimal value.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32041736","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.13","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"In 2008, there were no beavers in Scotland, as they had become extinct. In 2009, beavers were introduced from Norway. Surveys were carried out in the region of Tayside to monitor t","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"13","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.9—HL modelling functions","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Use of technology to solve systems of linear equations and polynomial equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}